{
  "texts": [
    "Some studies also utilize machine learning models to integrate fuzzing with symbolic execution.",
    "For example, Ref.",
    "[431] predicted the timing for switching between concrete and symbolic executions.",
    "[432] trained a neural network-based fuzzing policy on the dataset generated by symbolic execution, enabling the application of the learned policy to fuzz new programs.",
    "JOpFuzzer [433] learns the relationships between code features and optimization choices to direct seed mutation for JIT compiler fuzzing.The challenge here is similar to incorporating deep learning within static analysis: an excessive amount of expensive queries may outweigh simply exercising more test cases.Machine learning models generally perform better for domain-specific test input generation."
  ]
}